<setup>
  <selectFromSequence name="M" from="9" to="11" step="1"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="K" from="5" to="7" step="1"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="r" from="0.3" to="0.5" step="0.1"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="c" from="4.2" to="6.2" step="0.4"/>
  <number name="cplus">$c+$r/($K)</number>
   
  <function name="f" symbolic="false" >
    $M/(1+$K*exp(-1*$r*x))
  </function>

  <derivative name="fP" symbolic="false">
    $f
  </derivative>  

  <derivative name="fPP" symbolic="false">
    $fP
  </derivative>  
  
  <function name="L" symbolic="false" styleNumber="2">
    $$f($c) + $$fP($c)*(x-$c)
  </function>

</setup>

<p>
  An object moving along a straight line path has a differentiable position function <m>y=s(t)</m>; its position <m>s(t)</m> is measured in feet away from its starting location, <m>s(0) = 0</m>, and time is measured in seconds.  
</p>
<p>
  Suppose that at time <m>t=$c</m> seconds, the object's position is <m>s($c)=$$f($c)</m> feet. Furthermore, the object's instantaneous velocity at <m>t=$c</m> is <m>s'($c)=$$fP($c)</m> feet per second, and its acceleration at the same instant is <m>s''($c)=$$fPP($c)</m> feet per second per second.</p>
<p>
  <ol marker="a.">
    <li>
      <p>
        Use the local linearization to estimate the position of the object at <m>t=$cplus</m>.
      </p>  
      <p>
        <m>s($cplus) \approx </m><answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.1" allowedErrorIsAbsolute>$$L($cplus)</answer>
      </p>  
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        The estimate generated by the tangent line in part (a) is likely     
        <answer>
          <choiceInput name="overunder" inline>
            <choice>greater than</choice>
            <choice>less than</choice>
            <choice>equal to</choice>
          </choiceInput>            
            <award>
              <when>$overunder.selectedIndices=1 and $$fPP($c) < 0    
              </when>
            </award>  
            <award>
              <when>$overunder.selectedIndices=2 and $$fPP($c) > 0 
              </when> 
            </award>
          </answer> 
          the true value of <m>s($cplus)</m>, since <m>s''($c)</m> is 
          <answer>
            <choiceInput name="reason1" inline>
              <choice>positive</choice>
              <choice>zero</choice>
              <choice>negative</choice>
            </choiceInput>            
              <award>
                <when>$reason1.selectedIndices=1 and $$fPP($c) > 0       
                </when>
              </award>  
              <award>
                <when>$reason1.selectedIndices=3 and $$fPP($c) < 0 
                </when>
              </award>
          </answer>, so near <m>t = $c</m>, <m>s</m> is
          <answer>
            <choiceInput name="reason2" inline>
              <choice>concave up</choice>
              <choice>linear</choice>
              <choice>concave down</choice>
            </choiceInput>            
              <award>
                <when>$reason1.selectedIndices=1 and $$fPP($c) > 0       
                </when>
              </award>  
              <award>
                <when>$reason2.selectedIndices=3 and $$fPP($c) < 0 
                </when>
              </award>
          </answer>, which makes the tangent line to <m>s</m> at the point <m>($c,s($c))</m> lie
     <answer>
            <choiceInput name="reason3" inline>
              <choice>below</choice>
              <choice>above</choice>
            </choiceInput>            
              <award>
                <when>$reason3.selectedIndices=2 and $$fPP($c) < 0    
                </when>
              </award>  
              <award>
                <when>$reason3.selectedIndices=1 and $$fPP($c) > 0 
                </when> 
              </award>
      </answer>   
    the curve.
        </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        In everyday language, describe the behavior of the moving object at the instant <m>t=$cplus</m> by filling in the following blanks appropriately. 
      </p>
      <p>
        When <m>t=$cplus</m>, the object is 
        <answer>
          <choiceInput name="choice1" inline>
            <choice>moving away from</choice>
            <choice>staying the same distance from</choice>
            <choice>moving toward</choice>
          </choiceInput>            
            <award>
              <when>$choice1.selectedIndices=1 and $$fP($c) > 0    
              </when>
            </award>  
            <award>
              <when>$choice1.selectedIndices=3 and $$fP($c) < 0 
              </when> 
            </award>
          </answer> 
          the origin, since its velocity <m>s'($c)</m> is 
          <answer>
            <choiceInput name="choice2" inline>
              <choice>positive</choice>
              <choice>zero</choice>
              <choice>negative</choice>
            </choiceInput>            
              <award>
                <when>$choice2.selectedIndices=1 and $$fP($c) > 0       
                </when>
              </award>  
              <award>
                <when>$choice2.selectedIndices=3 and $$fP($c) < 0 
                </when>
              </award>
          </answer>; in addition, the object is
          <answer>
            <choiceInput name="choice3" inline>
              <choice>speeding up</choice>
              <choice>maintaining constant speed</choice>
              <choice>slowing down</choice>
            </choiceInput>            
              <award>
                <when>$choice3.selectedIndices=1 and $$fPP($c) > 0       
                </when>
              </award>  
              <award>
                <when>$choice3.selectedIndices=3 and $$fPP($c) < 0 
                </when>
              </award>
          </answer>, since its acceleration <m>s''($c)</m> is
     <answer>
            <choiceInput name="choice4" inline>
              <choice>positive</choice>
              <choice>zero</choice>
              <choice>negative</choice>
            </choiceInput>            
              <award>
                <when>$choice4.selectedIndices=3 and $$fPP($c) < 0    
                </when>
              </award>  
              <award>
                <when>$choice4.selectedIndices=1 and $$fPP($c) > 0 
                </when> 
              </award>
      </answer>   
        
      </p>
    </li>
  </ol>

</p>  